    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.81-82_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">8<del>2</del><add>1</add></fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        1460 Washington Ave
                        San Jose 25, California
                        May 14, 1958
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt, Jr</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Rt 6</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to the letter I wrote you about a year ago asking about <hi rend="caps">TV</hi> rights on parts of your book <hi rend="caps">WHEN THE TREE FLOWERED</hi> wish to advise that I wrote off the chapter <hi rend="caps">THE BOYS WHO HA<del>S</del><add>D</add> SISTER TROUBLE</hi> have not yet received any favorable action.</p>
                
                <p>I went to Hollywood to one of the best agents there, leaving my copy of your book, with the idea <del>a</del><add>t</add>hat if they could do anything with any other part they could contact<del>t</del> you direct but they returned the book the other day so that probably is not a good prospect any more. Do hope we can put over the seperate story about the boys though and will let you know if anything develops.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With best wishes for your good health and greetings to your wife, I am,</salute>
                
                    <salute>Yours sincerely,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Verna Moxley Smith</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <opener><hi rend="caps">P.S.</hi></opener> <p>am enclosing clipping that might possibly interest you.</p>
                </postscript>
                
                <postscript>
                    <p>Am still working on
                    getting <hi rend="caps">WIND 'TIL SUNDOWN</hi>
                    sold to movies too.</p>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.81-82_0002"/>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    <hi rend="caps">VERNA MOXLEY SMITH</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    1460 Washington Avenue
                        <lb/>
                    San Jose 25, California
                </ab>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">8<del>3</del><add>2</add></fw>
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    SAN JOSE
                    MAY 14
                    9 PM
                    1958
                    2 CALIF.
                </ab>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>3? Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>U.S. POSTAG<unclear reason="missing" cert="high">E</unclear> <unclear reason="missing">3Â¢</unclear>
                    IN GOD WE TR<unclear reason="missing" cert="high">UST</unclear>
                    LIBERTY</p>
                </figure>
                
                <ab type="address">
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <del/><add><hi rend="caps">G.</hi></add> Neihardt, Jr</addrLine>
                            <addrLine><del>Route 6</del></addrLine> 
                                <addrLine><del>Columbia, Missouri</del></addrLine>
